### (re) Learning Digital Design
After having written a partially complete emulator for the 8086 processor, I came to realize a few things. One, while I understand enough to implement about 95% of the processor, I don't understand the remaining 5% at all. Two, there's a lot of stuff that I'd like to brush up on and learn when it comes to electronics. While I may be a CS major, I'm really interested in computer architecture and the electronics that is involved in it. So I've started studying from the basics, from Digital Design and plan on achieving some level of mastery and understanding in the subject. Hopefully this will help in landing a job in this field, which I prefer any day over somthing like Web-Development (no offense to anyone, but I just don't like that field).

### Reading the Gita
I never thought I'd be reading /The Gita/.
Its not that I didn't want to read it or anything, its just that I'm not really a religious person and I thought reading a fat book related to something I don't believe in is a waste of time. Well, I'm reading it now anyways. While my beliefs have not changed, I do think it was unfair of me to have assumed that I can't learn anything from the Gita. I'm reading it chapter by chapter, taking whatever lessons I think are valuable and keeping aside things that I don't think are of much use to me. Who knows? Maybe when I'm done reading it, I may end up changing some aspects of my life. Since I don't see any harm in simply reading\/analysing a book, I'm just going ahead and doing it 😁.
